As said >>48920442, a lid helps enormously.

Another thing I find helps is I use a fairly low temperature on the stove. Like, normally the dial goes from lo to 1 to 10 to high heat. By using about a 4, the pan heats through and the lid traps the heat so the cheese gets a chance to heat & melt thoroughly while the bread toasts slowly. By the time I flip the sandwich two or three times to cool off the side that's in contact with the pan, I usually get a nice, crisp golden brown toast with cheese melting out the sides and sizzling on the pan. Worth the extra three or five minutes for the perfection of grilled cheese well done.
